In index.html, fix the Goals ticker so the text doesn't overlap when it switches. Replace the dual-row slide animation with a single-row crossfade that swaps text in place every 5 seconds.

1. In the <style> block, find this CSS:

.goal-ticker-row {
  position: absolute; inset: 0;
  display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 12.5px; font-weight: 600;
  font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
  color: var(--text-primary);
  white-space: nowrap;
}
.goal-ticker-row.is-leaving  { animation: ticker-leave 0.45s cubic-bezier(0.55, 0, 0.55, 1) forwards; }
.goal-ticker-row.is-entering { animation: ticker-enter 0.45s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1) forwards; }
@keyframes ticker-leave { from { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); } to { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(-100%); } }
@keyframes ticker-enter { from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(100%); } to { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); } }

Replace it with:

.goal-ticker-row {
  position: absolute; inset: 0;
  display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 8px;
  font-family: var(--font-mono);
  font-size: 12.5px; font-weight: 600;
